    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="372"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7504</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chinese Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Soong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="17" xml:id="d372fn17">Copy transmitted to the Department on
                        March 25 by the Treasury Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-21">March 21,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: In connection with the
                    Agreement between the Governments of the United States of America and the
                    Republic of China regarding financial aid to China,<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d372fn18">See bracketed note, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                    </note> as a manifestation <pb facs="0500" n="490" xml:id="pg_490"/> of the
                    cooperative spirit which underlies the common war effort of our two countries, I
                    wish to inform you that it is the intention of my Government, through the
                    Minister of Finance, to keep you fully informed from time to time as to the use
                    of the funds provided in the said Agreement.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tse Vun Soong</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For joint statement by the Secretary of the Treasury (Morgenthau) and the
                        Chinese Minister for Foreign Affairs (Soong) and text of agreement signed at
                        Washington, March 21, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                            >Bulletin</hi>, March 28, 1942, page 263, or <hi rend="italic">United
                            States Relations With China</hi>, page 510.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
